    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Before railroads arrived, Apalachicola was the third‑busiest Gulf port, trailing only New Orleans and Mobile.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        11
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apalachicola%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The John Gorrie Memorial Bridge, originally built in 1935 and rebuilt in 1988, carries U.S. Highway 98 over the Apalachicola River.",
